args.description:
(Optional) Each scope will be muted until the given POSIX timestamp or forever if the value is 0.
To mute the alert completely:
silenced = {
  "*" =  0
}
To mute role:db for a short time:
silenced = {
  "role:db" = 1412798116
}
Note: due to HCL limitations, it is impossible to use interpolations in keys.
For example, the following will result in muting the scope role:${var:role} (no interpolation is done):
silenced = {
    "role:${var:role}" = 0
}
To workaround this, you can use the map function of HCL:
silenced = ${map("role:${var:role}", 0)}
